# F4 DUAL-RUN expected-divergence list (specs/v2.2-p6.5-dualrun.sh).
#
# The dual-run gate compares the FULL production path — `bin/ssc run P` (default front) vs
# `SSC_FRONT=F bin/ssc run P` (F) — capturing (exit, stdout). It is GREEN when every divergence is
# listed here; an UNEXPECTED divergence (F worse than the default front, not listed) is a genuine-FAIL.
#
# ★ SINCE THE F4a DELEGATE-FALLBACK (RunNativeV2), the UNBOUND-GLOBAL gap classes fall back cleanly:
# where F cannot lower a program it emits an unbound global, `Reader.validate` catches it, and RunNativeV2
# re-lowers the file through the default front → EQUAL. The residuals below are the class the fallback
# CANNOT catch: F resolves all globals but lowers a VALUE wrong, so the pre-check passes and F runs to a
# wrong result. On the DEFAULT slice: 43/43 EQUAL, 0 divergence.
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FULL-CORPUS SWEEP 2026-07-21 (SSC_DUALRUN_ALL=1, 521 programs): initially EQUAL 509/521, 10 real residuals,
#   all one class = F's MULTI-FILE (import) lowering. RECONCILED as fixes land — now 3 residuals:
#   FIXED: multi-link-imports, money-multisection, money-portable-v2, tkv2-theme-css-vars (import-order fix
#          70d5bbabf); std-bifunctor (extension-member collection fix — F now collects EVERY member of a
#          given-nested `extension` group); tagless-sealed-dispatch (dispatcher-arity fix — a same-named
#          extension method in a `given` AND standalone: the standalone impl is now emitted as
#          `m__ext_default` and the bare `m` dispatcher delegates its fallback to it, mirroring ssc1-lower);
#          tagless-multi-file (given-body extension block must END at the first `;`-separated plain `def`:
#          `skipExtBodyZ` consumed the depth-0 `;` so `collectOMExtMs` mis-glued Monad's plain `def log`/`pure`
#          as an extension member — receiver-prepended arity N+1 + a spurious bare dispatcher; now the `;` is
#          KEPT as the block boundary; verified byte-identical output F-vs-default on the real multi-file path);
#          litdoc (single-arg `String.substring(from)` lowered to `sslice` with only 2 args — the end index
#          was dropped, so the runtime `sslice` prim read `args(2)` and crashed with `ssc: 2`
#          (IndexOutOfBoundsException). Now, per ssc1-lower, a 1-arg substring appends `(prim slen recv)` as
#          the end; verified byte-identical output F-vs-default on the real flattened litdoc).
#   REMAINING 2 (below): mcp-types, std-monaderror. Each now
#          blocked by a DIFFERENT residual bug (object-varargs, a monaderror
#          None-match) — see the per-entry BUGS refs. dsl-ast-builder FIXED 2026-07-21 (extension
#          top-level members no longer swallow following defs; F now byte-identical to default).
#   The flip stays BLOCKED until these are fixed; the F4a fallback cannot catch them (globals resolve,
#   values are wrong). http-client / scljet-sql-orderby-expr were FALSE divergences (see NON-RESIDUAL).
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# format (TAB-separated):  <BUCKET>\t<program>\t<reason>
#   buckets: GAP (real F residual — needs multi-file lowering fix) / OUT / DEFERRED /
#            FLAKY (non-deterministic program, cannot byte-compare — NOT an F bug) /
#            SLOW  (F correct but slower than the sweep timeout — a FALSE timeout, NOT an F bug)
# NOTE: the gate's isGap() matches by program NAME in ANY bucket, so FLAKY/SLOW entries also suppress the
#   fail. A future REAL regression on a FLAKY/SLOW program would be masked — re-verify by hand if suspect.

# ── GAP — RUNTIME-CORRECTNESS residuals. MULTI-FILE programs where F's lowering of imported values is
#    WRONG while all globals resolve (static pre-check passes → F runs to a wrong result). NOT fallback-
#    catchable: a run-time rerun is unsafe (side-effect duplication; ~half the corpus is multi-file incl.
#    scljet DB writers). These need F's MULTI-FILE lowering fixed. Each verified DETERMINISTIC (F run twice,
#    identical) in a clean F-staged worktree on 2026-07-21. ──
# RECONCILED 2026-07-21 (10 → 6). FIXED and removed: multi-link-imports, money-multisection, money-portable-v2,
# tkv2-theme-css-vars (F import-order fix 70d5bbabf); std-bifunctor (extension-member fix — F now collects ALL
# members of a given-nested `extension` group, not just the 1st). Remaining 6 below.
GAP	mcp-types	multi-file (imports std/mcp/types.ssc): F object-method vararg call → `arity: 1 expected, 2 given`, rc=1 after partial output; default prints full 107 B. See BUGS f-object-method-varargs.
GAP	std-monaderror	multi-file (imports std/either.ssc, std/monaderror.ssc): the 2-instance `handleError` dispatcher bug is FIXED (dispatcher-arity fix); F now advances past it to a SEPARATE `match: no arm for None/0` bug, rc=1; default prints 192 B. See BUGS f-monaderror-none-match.

# ── NON-RESIDUALS — divergences the sweep flagged that are NOT F correctness bugs (adjudicated 2026-07-21;
#    listed so the full-corpus gate stays green, with the evidence to re-verify). ──
FLAKY	http-client	NETWORK non-determinism — the program's own output varies run-to-run (F1 rc=1 15 B vs F2 rc=1 0 B; default rc=124 timeout in the sweep vs rc=1 11 B on re-run). A non-deterministic program cannot be byte-compared; NOT an F bug.
SLOW	scljet-sql-orderby-expr	FALSE TIMEOUT — at DR_TIMEOUT≥150 F output is BYTE-IDENTICAL to default (sha ae1324ba, 335 B, verified twice). The sweep's 60s timeout was too short for F on this heavy scljet DB program (F rc=124). F is CORRECT here, just slower; NOT a residual. Raise DR_TIMEOUT for scljet in full sweeps.
